Source code for poc_project.models.RequestLogModel

from sqlmodel import Field, SQLModel




[docs]
class RequestLog(SQLModel, table=True):
    """
    Represents a log entry for a request processed by an application.

    Attributes:
        id: An optional integer field representing the unique identifier of the log entry. It is set as the primary key of the table and can be automatically generated by the database.
        path: A string field representing the path of the request (e.g., "/api/users").
        processing_time: A float field representing the time taken to process the request in seconds.
    """

    id: int | None = Field(default=None, primary_key=True)
    path: str
    processing_time: float
